stylometry: A dilemma is depending on the amount of products you order, market demand fluxuates all the time, so there may be holding costs (inventory) costs if too much product is ordered, the customer finds a better alternative, or that product is dated because a new one came out, etc. The trade off is that you could sell alot more product because you ordered more, or on the other hand, in a severe situation that product you ordered could end up costing you more in the end because of inventory costs and then having to put that product on sale to get it to sell.
